15:32.390 --> 15:36.061
I juiced him.
Or he juiced me.

15:36.061 --> 15:38.104
- I guess.
- What is that?

15:38.104 --> 15:40.940
If you touch Currents
in a certain way,

15:40.940 --> 15:42.859
you can take a little bit
of energy from them.

15:42.859 --> 15:44.611
Remember how tired I just was?

15:44.611 --> 15:47.864
- Yeah.
- I feel pretty good now.

15:47.864 --> 15:50.909
The downside is, you do
take that energy from them.

15:50.909 --> 15:52.577
But when it's
a piece of shit like this,

15:52.577 --> 15:54.871
I don't feel so bad.

15:54.871 --> 15:56.831
- Wow.
- [laughs]

15:56.831 --> 15:58.458
You should try it.

15:58.458 --> 16:00.543
I don't know.
It seems wrong.

16:00.543 --> 16:03.505
Nothing really
happens to him long-term...

16:03.505 --> 16:05.173
I don't think.

16:14.766 --> 16:16.643
Try to feel for his pulse.

16:16.643 --> 16:17.727
Okay.

16:18.728 --> 16:20.939
Using this as a guide,

16:20.939 --> 16:24.192
try and get on the same
wavelength as him,

16:24.192 --> 16:25.694
if that makes sense.

16:25.694 --> 16:27.320
Close your eyes if it helps.

16:32.158 --> 16:33.952
He just feels gross and clammy.

16:33.952 --> 16:35.829
Uh, okay, maybe this will help.

16:38.540 --> 16:39.958
What are you doing?

16:39.958 --> 16:41.334
Just relax.

16:42.544 --> 16:45.505
Now try and make it feel like
you're breathing him in

16:45.505 --> 16:47.590
through your hand.

16:47.590 --> 16:51.720
♪ ♪

16:51.720 --> 16:53.888
Ooh, ooh, wait.
Mama feeling something.

16:53.888 --> 16:56.474
[chuckles]
Keep...keep going.

16:56.474 --> 17:00.019
[phone rings]

17:00.019 --> 17:03.314
I told you not to call me.
It's not my weekend.

17:03.314 --> 17:06.025
Ugh, well, then feed him
some chicken nuggets, bitch.

17:06.025 --> 17:07.610
[phone clatters]

17:07.610 --> 17:12.907
♪ ♪

17:12.907 --> 17:14.993
[both groan]

17:14.993 --> 17:16.745
- Holy shit!
- Whoa.

17:16.745 --> 17:18.997
- What did you do?
- He made me mad!

17:18.997 --> 17:21.624
[laughing] I've never made him
pass out like that.

17:21.624 --> 17:23.918
- Is he okay?
- Yeah, he's still breathing.

17:23.918 --> 17:25.378
He'll be okay.

17:25.378 --> 17:27.630
Oh, my God, do you feel that?

17:27.630 --> 17:30.717
- Yeah, I sure do.
- [laughs]

17:30.717 --> 17:33.428
- [whoops]
- [giggling]

17:33.428 --> 17:35.972
- Oh, it's so nice out.
- [sighs]

17:35.972 --> 17:38.099
So pretty.

17:38.099 --> 17:39.934
Ooh, watch this.
Ready?

17:39.934 --> 17:41.269
- Yeah.
- Watch.

17:41.269 --> 17:43.021
- [moaning]
- [laughs]

17:43.021 --> 17:44.522
Does it look like
I'm kissing him?

17:44.522 --> 17:46.149
You know what's funny?

17:46.149 --> 17:47.776
He doesn't know
what's happening.

17:47.776 --> 17:49.861
[both giggling]

17:49.861 --> 17:52.322
Oh, yeah, baby.

17:52.322 --> 17:53.948
What is that,
the cheap unleaded?

17:53.948 --> 17:55.742
Yeah, that's how I like it.

17:55.742 --> 17:57.202
Hey, where are you going?

17:57.202 --> 17:58.995
Can you please get me
some Twizzlers?

17:58.995 --> 18:00.288
I love you.

18:00.288 --> 18:02.040
He doesn't like you anymore.

18:02.040 --> 18:03.666
[both laughing]

18:03.666 --> 18:05.710
Oh, my God, this feels so good.

18:05.710 --> 18:07.086
- Hey.
- What?

18:07.086 --> 18:09.088
Do you ever see faces
in things?

18:09.088 --> 18:10.715
What do you mean?

18:10.715 --> 18:12.425
You see this electricity meter?

18:12.425 --> 18:14.636
And the two dial-y things
are the eyes...

18:14.636 --> 18:16.304
and the pipe is the mouth.

18:16.304 --> 18:17.722
Oh.

18:17.722 --> 18:20.725
[Kase] I know.
[June] Aww, he's cute.

18:20.725 --> 18:22.143
I love this game.

18:22.143 --> 18:23.978
[laughs]
I know.

18:23.978 --> 18:25.814
Look, there's one over here.

18:25.814 --> 18:27.565
- Where?
- Look. That mop.

18:27.565 --> 18:29.943
See, it's like a...
an angry lady with crazy hair.

18:29.943 --> 18:32.904
Yeah. Ohh.

18:32.904 --> 18:34.405
That is good.

18:34.405 --> 18:36.032
That is...you are good.

18:36.032 --> 18:38.034
That was a really good.
That's way better than that.

18:38.034 --> 18:39.661
- I agree.
- [both laugh]

18:39.661 --> 18:41.704
Are you the kind of person
who's really good at things

18:41.704 --> 18:43.206
the first time you try them?

18:43.206 --> 18:45.041
No one has ever said that
to me before.

18:45.041 --> 18:47.043
- No way.
- I swear.

18:47.043 --> 18:49.796
Yes, you are.
You're so good at this,

18:49.796 --> 18:52.590
and you are good at sewing,
and you're good

18:52.590 --> 18:54.968
at juicing the fuck out
of that asshole in there.

18:54.968 --> 18:56.678
- That's true.
- Yeah.

18:56.678 --> 18:58.638
Hey, do you think anyone
ever juiced us

18:58.638 --> 19:00.056
when we were Currents?

19:00.056 --> 19:02.100
I don't know.
Maybe.

19:02.100 --> 19:04.602
I did always get tired at,
like, 3:00 p.m.

19:04.602 --> 19:06.437
but I also ate a lot
of burritos at lunch.

19:16.781 --> 19:18.199
[clears throat]

19:20.076 --> 19:21.870
Oh hey, uh,

19:21.870 --> 19:23.913
I brought out some Reggie! Bars
if..if you want any.

19:23.913 --> 19:25.874
Oh, wow.
[laughs]

19:25.874 --> 19:29.335
[gasps] They stopped
making these years ago.

19:29.335 --> 19:32.881
Yeah, they just
show up in my kitchen.

19:32.881 --> 19:34.757
A lot of broccoli
shows up for me.

19:34.757 --> 19:37.635
I don't even like it that much.
Gives me gas.

19:40.680 --> 19:42.015
Hmm.

19:43.808 --> 19:46.436
So did anything ever happen
with Gold Diamond?

19:46.436 --> 19:48.855
- You guys were the best.
- Oh, no.

19:48.855 --> 19:51.524
No, I mean, we played
a few shows, but then...

19:51.524 --> 19:52.984
Jenny tried to
have sex with Steve,

19:52.984 --> 19:54.485
and then Steve
had sex with Josh,

19:54.485 --> 19:56.613
and the whole thing
just fell apart.

19:56.613 --> 19:59.032
So my uncle helped me
get a job at the gas company.

19:59.032 --> 20:00.617
I was there for 35 years.

20:02.702 --> 20:04.329
- Cool.
- [softly] Yeah.

20:05.622 --> 20:07.081
Even though you were
a couple years ahead of me,

20:07.081 --> 20:08.958
we had to know
some of the same people.

20:08.958 --> 20:10.585
Did you know
the Colito brothers?

20:10.585 --> 20:13.296
- Oh, yeah, I knew Rocky.
- I knew Ricky.

20:13.296 --> 20:15.214
Why would you name your kids
Ricky and Rocky? I don't...

20:15.214 --> 20:18.217
I know, and they had a sister
who was also named Riki.

20:18.217 --> 20:19.719
R-I-K-I.

20:19.719 --> 20:21.763
[giggles]
That's insane.

20:21.763 --> 20:23.181
What ended up
happening to them?

20:23.181 --> 20:25.099
Rocky got a girl pregnant
and dropped out

20:25.099 --> 20:27.393
to work at a car dealership.

20:27.393 --> 20:29.938
- Did you know Gina Levesque?
- Yeah, yeah, I did.

20:29.938 --> 20:31.439
- What happened to her?
- She got pregnant

20:31.439 --> 20:33.066
and dropped out.

20:33.066 --> 20:35.068
- Carrie Sowalski?
- Pregnant and dropped out.

20:35.068 --> 20:36.569
- Lisa Fargus?
- Pregnant,

20:36.569 --> 20:37.987
but she stayed in school.

20:37.987 --> 20:40.073
She went into labor
in fifth period.

20:40.073 --> 20:41.699
[laughs softly]

20:41.699 --> 20:43.242
[sighs]

20:43.242 --> 20:45.536
- I did not like Lisa Fargus.
- Yeah, no.

20:45.536 --> 20:48.498
I think she and her friends
keyed my Camaro.

20:48.498 --> 20:51.751
And I took really good care
of that car until...

20:51.751 --> 20:54.045
- You know.
- Yeah.

20:54.045 --> 20:56.673
If you don't my asking,
what happened?

20:56.673 --> 20:58.466
It's not much of story, really.

20:58.466 --> 21:00.677
I was going to
the grocery store for my mom,

21:00.677 --> 21:03.346
and I reached down to change
the station on the radio,

21:03.346 --> 21:07.475
and I looked back up,
and that was it.

21:07.475 --> 21:08.893
How'd you go?

21:08.893 --> 21:11.938
Lung cancer.
Nothing too interesting.

21:11.938 --> 21:13.982
All those cigarettes,
they ended up costing me

21:13.982 --> 21:15.358
in the long run.

21:17.068 --> 21:18.486
Well, if it makes you
feel any better,

21:18.486 --> 21:20.780
they did make you
look really cool.

21:20.780 --> 21:22.907
It's why every guy in
the school had a crush on you.

21:22.907 --> 21:24.575
- That's not true.
- Seriously.

21:24.575 --> 21:25.994
You were every
freshman guy's dream.

21:25.994 --> 21:27.328
[laughing]
Stop.

21:27.328 --> 21:29.122
I used to draw pictures of you.

21:29.122 --> 21:31.290
Not naked or anything.

21:31.290 --> 21:33.543
That's creepy.
I shouldn't have said that.

21:33.543 --> 21:36.546
That's okay.
We were kids.

21:40.425 --> 21:42.135
Do you want to listen
to some records?

21:42.135 --> 21:43.553
Yeah, sure.

21:51.686 --> 21:54.397
[♪ Climax Blues Band:
"Couldn't Get It Right"]

21:54.397 --> 21:57.400
Oh, my God.
Oh, I love this song.

21:57.400 --> 21:58.818
Cool.

21:58.818 --> 22:01.320
♪ ♪

22:01.320 --> 22:02.739
[man]
♪ Time was drifting... ♪

22:02.739 --> 22:04.782
This is weird, but...

22:04.782 --> 22:06.951
do you wanna dance, maybe?

22:06.951 --> 22:08.786
Sure.

22:08.786 --> 22:10.997
[laughs]

22:10.997 --> 22:13.166
[man]
♪ Restless feeling ♪

22:13.166 --> 22:15.960
♪ Really got a hold ♪

22:15.960 --> 22:18.087
♪ I started searching
for a better way ♪

22:18.087 --> 22:19.672
[laughs]

22:19.672 --> 22:22.341
Check you out.

22:22.341 --> 22:24.260
[man] ♪ But I kept on
looking for a sign ♪

22:24.260 --> 22:26.554
♪ In the middle of the night ♪

22:26.554 --> 22:28.890
♪ But I couldn't
see the light ♪

22:28.890 --> 22:31.851
♪ No I couldn't
see the light ♪

22:31.851 --> 22:33.561
♪ I kept on
looking for a way ♪

22:33.561 --> 22:36.189
♪ To take me
through the night ♪

22:36.189 --> 22:38.274
♪ I couldn't get it right ♪

22:38.274 --> 22:41.027
♪ I couldn't get it right ♪♪

22:41.027 --> 22:48.034
♪ ♪

22:58.961 --> 23:00.213
[man]
You figured it out.

23:04.550 --> 23:06.469
Is he talking to us?

23:06.469 --> 23:08.387
Can you see us?

23:08.387 --> 23:10.765
Where are you headed?

23:10.765 --> 23:12.391
We're going home.

23:12.391 --> 23:14.602
Seems to me
you're headed the wrong way.

23:15.561 --> 23:18.815
Uh, no,
Riverside is back that way.

23:18.815 --> 23:19.857
Didn't say it wasn't.

23:19.857 --> 23:21.192
Just said,

23:21.192 --> 23:23.528
"You're headed the wrong way."

23:23.528 --> 23:24.821
What are you talking about?

23:25.905 --> 23:30.076
There's another place.
You might find it interesting.

23:30.076 --> 23:32.662
Where is it?
What is it?

23:32.662 --> 23:34.413
Oh, down the road.

23:34.413 --> 23:36.499
If you're looking for answers,
you might walk along with me.

23:37.667 --> 23:39.210
Uh...
[laughs softly]

23:39.210 --> 23:41.254
I don't...I don't know.

23:41.254 --> 23:44.132
Oh, come on, come on.
You're not even curious?

23:44.132 --> 23:45.716
We should at least
check it out.

23:45.716 --> 23:47.135
He's saying
there's another place.

23:47.135 --> 23:48.719
- This is huge.
- We don't even know

23:48.719 --> 23:49.720
who this guy is.

23:49.720 --> 23:51.097
Sir?

23:51.097 --> 23:53.391
Who are you?
What is your name?

23:53.391 --> 23:55.268
You're still thinking
the wrong way.

23:55.268 --> 23:57.645
All right,
I'm not doing this.

23:57.645 --> 23:59.313
Oscar's back at home.
We can't just wander off...

23:59.313 --> 24:00.940
[whispering]
...with some creepy dude.

24:00.940 --> 24:02.692
[whispering] This might be
our only chance to do this,

24:02.692 --> 24:04.110
and get some more answers.

24:04.110 --> 24:05.903
Why don't I go home,
get Oscar,

24:05.903 --> 24:07.613
come back,
and we can talk about this?

24:07.613 --> 24:09.532
[man]
This place isn't for him.

24:09.532 --> 24:11.534
It's for you.

24:12.743 --> 24:14.287
Come on, June.

24:14.287 --> 24:16.664
We know what's back home.

24:16.664 --> 24:19.041
And here's this guy saying
all this cool shit.

24:19.041 --> 24:20.626
Come on.
Let's go.

24:20.626 --> 24:22.795
I can't.

24:22.795 --> 24:25.756
You are bored in Riverside.
I'm bored in Riverside.

24:25.756 --> 24:27.008
Why do you think that is?

24:27.008 --> 24:28.634
I don't know.

24:28.634 --> 24:30.678
Well, maybe there's a reason.

24:30.678 --> 24:32.513
Maybe the two of us
don't belong there.

24:32.513 --> 24:34.140
Come on.

24:34.140 --> 24:35.766
Let's go.
Let's go.

24:36.934 --> 24:38.936
Please.

24:38.936 --> 24:41.105
I can't.

24:41.105 --> 24:42.773
I'm sorry.

24:42.773 --> 24:46.527
Oscar would never
do that to me.

24:46.527 --> 24:48.613
But if you want to go,

24:48.613 --> 24:50.656
I...I understand.

24:53.034 --> 24:55.870
No, I want to stay with you.

24:55.870 --> 24:57.580
I'll walk you home.

24:57.580 --> 25:01.167
Well, if you change your mind,
come back this way.

25:01.167 --> 25:04.462
All roads lead to Oceanside.

25:11.219 --> 25:12.220
[knocking at door]

25:17.308 --> 25:18.768
[Oscar] Hey.

25:18.768 --> 25:20.728
How'd it go?
I was a nervous wreck.

25:20.728 --> 25:23.022
Well,
we talked about high school.

25:23.022 --> 25:25.274
Everyone's lives
ended up pretty shitty.

25:25.274 --> 25:26.692
I'm actually
kind of glad I died.

25:26.692 --> 25:28.945
Great.
Sounds like a good start.

25:28.945 --> 25:31.697
Then we listened to records
and we danced a little bit.

25:31.697 --> 25:33.407
- That's amazing.
- Yeah.

25:33.407 --> 25:37.245
Then she started talking
about her husband, Ray.

25:37.245 --> 25:38.663
- Oh.
- Yeah, they were married

25:38.663 --> 25:41.332
for 40 years or something,
so...

25:41.332 --> 25:45.044
she's hoping that when he dies,
he ends up here, like June did.

25:45.044 --> 25:46.837
So I think we're just
gonna be friends.

25:46.837 --> 25:48.631
Oh.

25:48.631 --> 25:50.132
Oh, man.

25:50.132 --> 25:51.926
Sorry about that, buddy.

25:51.926 --> 25:54.178
That's fine.

25:54.178 --> 25:57.014
It just sucks 'cause
we had a really good time.

25:57.014 --> 25:58.766
She's so cool.

26:00.434 --> 26:02.103
Sometimes I think about

26:02.103 --> 26:04.522
how I'll never find someone
that cool for me, you know?

26:04.522 --> 26:06.565
Hey, that's not true.

26:08.025 --> 26:10.111
It's the fucking
Bee Gees' fault.

26:10.111 --> 26:12.363
They were on the radio
the night I crashed my car,

26:12.363 --> 26:14.282
and they were so shitty,
I had to look down

26:14.282 --> 26:16.200
and change the station.

26:18.035 --> 26:20.079
Look, I know you and June
have a lot of problems.

26:20.079 --> 26:23.291
- I don't know about a lot.
- But you're lucky she's here.

26:23.291 --> 26:25.459
No one else here has that.

26:25.459 --> 26:27.670
Everyone's alone.

26:27.670 --> 26:29.505
Why do you two
get to be together?

26:32.300 --> 26:34.302
I don't know.

26:36.762 --> 26:37.972
Anyways,
you were...you were right

26:37.972 --> 26:39.307
about where to put
the bike poster.

26:39.307 --> 26:41.225
I think I'm gonna
leave it that way.

26:41.225 --> 26:42.893
Great.

26:42.893 --> 26:46.647
Well, I'd love to make you
a chocolate sundae

26:46.647 --> 26:47.606
to make you feel better.

26:47.606 --> 26:48.524
Jesus, no.

26:48.524 --> 26:51.152
I'm leaving.

26:51.152 --> 26:52.903
- Rain check?
[Mark] No.

27:01.454 --> 27:04.457
[door opens, closes]

27:06.459 --> 27:07.543
Hey.

27:08.669 --> 27:10.546
[Oscar] Where have you been?

27:10.546 --> 27:12.965
Oh, out for a walk.

27:12.965 --> 27:15.301
Just...lost track of time.

27:15.301 --> 27:17.345
Ah, okay.

27:17.345 --> 27:19.513
Well, there's something
I wanted to show you.

27:19.513 --> 27:21.724
I didn't like that
we were fighting earlier,

27:21.724 --> 27:24.352
so I found a solution.

27:25.353 --> 27:26.771
Okay.

27:30.316 --> 27:32.318
"Tines up."

27:32.318 --> 27:35.446
And there's a little fork guy
pointing to an alarm clock.

27:35.446 --> 27:38.616
You know, like time...
tine, time.

27:38.616 --> 27:40.493
And, you know,
it's facing up.

27:40.493 --> 27:42.703
And, you know,
it's a play on words.

27:42.703 --> 27:44.497
Right.
I got it.

27:44.497 --> 27:46.957
So now, whoever puts
the utensils away...

27:46.957 --> 27:48.542
could be you,
could be me...

27:48.542 --> 27:50.628
will remember
to put it back the right way.

27:51.462 --> 27:53.506
Well, I appreciate the sign,

27:53.506 --> 27:56.425
but you do know that earlier,

27:56.425 --> 27:58.761
we weren't just talking
about forks, right?

27:58.761 --> 28:01.389
Yeah, I know that, but...

28:01.389 --> 28:03.057
this is about the forks.

28:05.726 --> 28:07.311
What's wrong?

28:07.311 --> 28:09.980
I feel like maybe you're not
getting how I'm feeling.

28:09.980 --> 28:11.774
Okay, then tell me.

28:14.652 --> 28:16.529
[sighs softly]

28:17.655 --> 28:19.365
I feel trapped.

28:21.659 --> 28:23.202
What do you mean?

28:23.202 --> 28:26.747
I mean,
we are actually trapped here.

28:26.747 --> 28:29.291
We can't go too far
from the fountain.

28:29.291 --> 28:32.128
I'm sorry,
that's just how it works here.

28:33.587 --> 28:36.590
How do we know
there's not something else

28:36.590 --> 28:38.008
- out there?
- Like what? What?

28:38.008 --> 28:40.010
I don't know,
something, anything.

28:40.010 --> 28:42.555
I've never heard anyone
talk about anything else.

28:42.555 --> 28:45.558
It's safe here.
It's nice.

28:45.558 --> 28:48.185
So you're telling me
that if you heard

28:48.185 --> 28:49.937
there was anywhere else,

28:49.937 --> 28:52.773
you still wouldn't go?

28:54.024 --> 28:55.484
I don't know.

28:55.484 --> 28:58.112
I like where we are.

28:58.112 --> 29:00.239
It's not so bad.
Look at this house.

29:00.239 --> 29:02.450
Look at the flow from
the kitchen to the living room.

29:02.450 --> 29:04.743
- It's seamless.
- I love this house.

29:04.743 --> 29:06.704
It's very well-decorated.

29:06.704 --> 29:09.582
And the bathroom here is
way better than what we had,

29:09.582 --> 29:12.835
but it is not about the house.

29:12.835 --> 29:17.173
We do the same things
every single day,

29:17.173 --> 29:20.718
and I don't see it changing

29:20.718 --> 29:23.554
literally forever.

29:23.554 --> 29:25.723
That bothers me.

29:25.723 --> 29:26.932
Well, I think
